# Coding standards (Radio Udaan)

## Intent
All code should look like it was written and maintained by the same engineering team — clear structure, restrained comments, no AI filler.

## Comments
- **File header**: one or two lines on what the module owns (Dart `///` doc on library/class; PHP `@package` block where the plugin already uses it).
- **Inline**: only for non-obvious behaviour — WordPress/Forminator contract, store-policy constraints, why a catch is swallowed, rate limits.
- Do **not** narrate obvious code (`// increment counter`). Do **not** leave commented-out blocks or bare `TODO` without context.

## Flutter (`radio_udaan_app/`)
- Product copy → `lib/core/constants/app_strings.dart`.
- Client metadata (version, platform) → `lib/core/constants/app_constants.dart` (keep **marketing version** aligned with `pubspec.yaml`; build number lives only in `pubspec.yaml` `version: X.Y.Z+BUILD`).
- **TestFlight / store builds**: increment `pubspec.yaml` build (`+NNN`) and update `.cursor/memory/release-state.md` in the **same commit** as app changes — never rely on a follow-up bump after CI 90189.
- REST errors → `parseApiError()` in `lib/core/network/dio_exception_mapper.dart`; UI shows `ApiError.message`.
- Debug-only UI (API base URL, dev hints) → wrap in `kDebugMode`.
- Accessibility: `Semantics` on controls; `liveRegion: true` for errors and success messages.
- Split large screens into `widgets/` when a file grows past ~300 lines of UI logic.

## WordPress plugin (`radioudaan-app-api/`)
- Match existing style: `defined( 'ABSPATH' ) || exit`, `WP_REST_Response` / `WP_Error`, text domain `radioudaan-app-api`.
- PHPDoc on public REST handlers and settings helpers.
- Log with `RadioUdaan_App_Logger`; never log phone numbers, OTP, or file paths with PII in production.

## Avoid
- Hardcoding Forminator fields or upload limits in the app.
- `READ_SMS` or broad storage permissions on Android.
- One-off “helper” classes used in a single place.
- Placeholder user strings (“coming soon”) on paths users can reach before release.
